sentences: Luciana Mocchi (born 8 June 1990) is a Uruguayan singer and composer.
In 2009 she won the "Canto Joven – Movida Joven 2009" award and a mention for best composition, granted by the Municipality of Montevideo.
In 2009 she won the "Canto Joven – Movida Joven 2009" award and a mention for best composition, granted by the Municipality of Montevideo.
The following year she received the same prize and a unique mention for composition.

In 2011, urged by singer and producer Lea Ben Sasson, she began recording La Velocidad del paisaje, her first studio material, preproduced by Martín Musotto, brother of the Argentine percussionist Ramiro Musotto.
In April 2014 she was the opening act for Paul McCartney at the Estadio Centenario in Montevideo, which was a turning point in the visibility of her career.

Mocchi was the executive producer of the documentary Botija de mi país (2013), which deals with the careers of ten Uruguayan musicians established in the United States, including José Serebrier, who was nominated 38 times for Grammy Awards, and won eight.
In November 2016 she presented her second album entitled Mañana será otro disco, with the participation of Fernando Cabrera, Julián Kartun, Andrés Beeuwsaert, and violinist Christine Brebes.
